  "img": "Art%20-%20Items/weapons/folken88_httpss.mj.run0eimiz3f53k_fantasy_sword_made_of_magic_2f30162b-58eb-4608-a1ac-ce2c8907f609_3.webp",
  "name": "Sea-Steel Blade",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<img src=\"Art%20-%20Items/weapons/folken88_httpss.mj.run0eimiz3f53k_fantasy_sword_made_of_magic_2f30162b-58eb-4608-a1ac-ce2c8907f609_3.webp\" /><p>Sea-Steel is a rare, magically hardened form of <strong data-start=\"363\" data-end=\"381\">deep-sea coral</strong> that is nearly <strong data-start=\"397\" data-end=\"438\">indistinguishable from polished steel</strong>, save for its <strong data-start=\"453\" data-end=\"479\">faint iridescent sheen</strong> that shifts between <strong data-start=\"500\" data-end=\"529\">blue-green and storm-gray</strong> under certain light. Found only in <strong data-start=\"565\" data-end=\"588\">deep ocean trenches</strong>, it is harvested and shaped by <strong data-start=\"620\" data-end=\"647\">sahuagin weapon forgers</strong>, who <strong data-start=\"653\" data-end=\"711\">infuse it with abyssal salts and elemental water magic</strong> to make it as strong as steel.</p><p data-start=\"746\" data-end=\"1046\"><strong data-start=\"746\" data-end=\"784\">Unlike normal coral, Sea-Steel is:</strong><br data-start=\"784\" data-end=\"787\" />✔ As <strong data-start=\"792\" data-end=\"812\">durable as steel</strong> but naturally <strong data-start=\"827\" data-end=\"838\">buoyant</strong>, making it easier to wield underwater.<br data-start=\"877\" data-end=\"880\" />✔ <strong data-start=\"882\" data-end=\"917\">Resistant to rust and corrosion</strong>, even in the harshest seawater.<br data-start=\"949\" data-end=\"952\" />✔ Retains a <strong data-start=\"964\" data-end=\"984\">razor-sharp edge</strong>, allowing for <strong data-start=\"999\" data-end=\"1043\">clean cuts through armor and flesh alike</strong>.</p><hr data-start=\"1048\" data-end=\"1051\" /><h3 data-start=\"1053\" data-end=\"1092\"><strong data-start=\"1057\" data-end=\"1090\">Sea-Steel Falchions in Battle</strong></h3><p data-start=\"1093\" data-end=\"1399\">These wickedly curved <strong data-start=\"1115\" data-end=\"1139\">masterwork falchions</strong> are <strong data-start=\"1144\" data-end=\"1163\">favored weapons</strong> among <strong data-start=\"1170\" data-end=\"1233\">sahuagin raiders, deep-sea reavers, and aquatic mercenaries</strong>. Each blade is <strong data-start=\"1249\" data-end=\"1271\">ritually inscribed</strong> with sahuagin runes of <strong data-start=\"1295\" data-end=\"1319\">hunger and dominance</strong>, and many are <strong data-start=\"1334\" data-end=\"1351\">stained black</strong> from the blood of countless surface-dwellers.</p><h4 data-start=\"1401\" data-end=\"1446\"><strong data-start=\"1406\" data-end=\"1446\">Special Effects (Sea-Steel Material)</strong></h4><ul data-start=\"1447\" data-end=\"2024\"><li data-start=\"1447\" data-end=\"1591\"><strong data-start=\"1449\" data-end=\"1468\">Buoyant Blades:</strong> When wielded <strong data-start=\"1482\" data-end=\"1496\">underwater</strong>, a Sea-Steel falchion does <strong data-start=\"1524\" data-end=\"1588\">not take the normal attack penalties for fighting underwater</strong>.</li></ul>",
      "instructions": "",
      "unidentified": "<p>This sword has one curved, sharp edge like a scimitar, with the back edge unsharpened and either flat or slightly curved. Its weight is greater toward the end, making it better for chopping rather than stabbing.</p>"
    },
